1
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:19,625
Maria's a teacher,

2
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:20,875
but she's not smart
enough to know

3
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,875
that eating junk food's
bad for your health.

4
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:24,208
That's all she ever eats.

5
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,541
She's gonna make
herself sick.

6
00:00:26,625 --> 00:00:29,291
It's not like we're the poster
children for health food.

7
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:31,458
Sorry, what was that?

8
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:32,958
As you know, you're
fortunate enough

9
00:00:33,041 --> 00:00:35,500
to travel in the company
of the great night tribe.

10
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:37,458
If you keep spending
your time hanging around

11
00:00:37,541 --> 00:00:39,208
an agent of the evil Church,

12
00:00:39,291 --> 00:00:41,250
I promise you,
it'll end in disaster.

13
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:53,916
Since my other half
is already awake.

14
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,208
I figured it
was only right

15
00:00:55,291 --> 00:00:56,583
that I got out
of bed as well,

16
00:00:56,666 --> 00:00:58,000
plus I'm starving.

17
00:00:58,083 --> 00:00:59,333
Good timing then.

18
00:00:59,416 --> 00:01:01,958
Hmm. Looks like you've put
together quite the feast

19
00:01:02,041 --> 00:01:04,500
this morning, haven't you?

20
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:06,750
It's not all for
breakfast actually.

21
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:08,166
Some of it's for lunch.

22
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:10,833
Well, well. Cooking
multiple meals?

23
00:01:10,916 --> 00:01:12,500
What have you
done with my bro?

24
00:01:12,583 --> 00:01:14,750
Have you finally recognized
how awesome I am

25
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:17,583
and decided to pay me the
respect I'm clearly owed?

26
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:19,583
I already told you
this yesterday.

27
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:21,375
That Maria girl
doesn't eat real food,

28
00:01:21,458 --> 00:01:22,916
all she ever eats is junk.

29
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,083
So I thought I'd help out
by making her a decent meal.

30
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:27,833
But don't worry.

31
00:01:27,916 --> 00:01:29,250
I made enough
for you, too.

32
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:32,333
So Maria's the priority

33
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:34,416
and I'm stuck here
playing second fiddle.

34
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,041
Wha'd you say?

35
00:01:36,125 --> 00:01:38,083
What do you care?

36
00:01:38,166 --> 00:01:40,041
Hey, where are you
running off to?

37
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:42,416
Your food'll get cold. Kobato!

38
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:47,041
My brother's dumb. Big time.

39
