00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:18,791
[Music]

48
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:21,083
"This time, the SAGA is
a Serious Battle"

49
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:27,375
Hey! Didn't expect
to see you so early!

50
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:28,625
Not again.

51
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:31,000
A person can't survive
on potato chips alone.

52
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:32,541
Speak for yourself!

53
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:33,833
These taste way better
than any of the other stuff

54
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:35,500
they have here.

55
00:03:35,583 --> 00:03:36,791
Check it out!

56
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,333
Woah.

57
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:40,166
That's a lotta chips.

58
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:42,750
Yozora lets me stock
up when I work for her.

59
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:44,125
You're like a pack rat.

60
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:46,250
Guess I shouldn't
be surprised.

61
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:47,791
Here.

62
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,041
Oh wow.

63
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,958
Did you make all
this just for me?

64
00:03:54,041 --> 00:03:55,958
That's very nice
of you, but--

65
00:03:56,041 --> 00:03:57,875
What's your angle, Kodaka?

66
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,583
People don't
just make food.

67
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:01,375
I don't have
an "angle", okay?

68
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:03,625
Just make sure
you return my box.

69
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:05,666
I'll make your lunch
for you tomorrow, too.

70
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,000
Wow.

71
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:08,083
You're really
being nice to me

72
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:10,333
outta the goodness
of your heart?

73
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:12,208
You must be some
kinda saint.

74
00:04:12,291 --> 00:04:14,375
I don't know what it
is, it's just that

75
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:17,416
you sorta remind me of my
sister when she was little.

76
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,416
I wanna look out for you.

77
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:22,625
I didn't know you actually
had a younger sister.

78
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,583
I guess it makes sense,
you are the big brother type.

79
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:26,958
Yeah, well.

80
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:29,208
I'd love to hang out,
but I gotta get to class.

81
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:31,541
Lay off the potato
chips, all right?

82
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:33,500
Okay, big bro! You got it!

83
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:36,458
Big bro?

84
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:40,583
I've heard a lot of rumors
about his dining habits.

85
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,791
Apparently, he always eats
his lunch before lunchtime.

86
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:46,666
Please accept
my apologies.

87
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:49,541
I'm so sorry my snack
didn't satisfy your hunger

88
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:50,916
That's not it.

89
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,958
But thank you though.

90
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:54,375
Big brother! Hey!

91
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:55,541
Guess what?

92
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:57,541
I ate my lunch and
it was so awesome!

93
00:04:57,625 --> 00:04:59,583
Yozora's yucky potato
chips taste like poo-poo

94
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,416
compared to what you made!

95
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,291
Poop-head Yozora makes
people eat nasty poo-poo chips!

96
00:05:04,375 --> 00:05:06,541
-Oh?
-I was just kidding around!

97
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:08,500
Your chips are the best!

98
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:10,916
It's weird to make a young
girl call you big bro!

99
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,125
Do you have some kinda

100
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:14,041
sexy 'little sister
fetish' or what?

101
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:16,416
No. And I'm not 'making'
her call me anything.

102
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,125
Kodaka really
is a big brother,

103
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:20,583
so I figured it would be
the perfect name for him.

104
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:26,666
Gosh.

105
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:29,166
Wouldn't it be awesome to
go inside a video game?

106
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,625
Uh, uh I mean, not really!

107
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:34,458
That was a joke. I
didn't really mean that.

108
00:05:34,541 --> 00:05:36,291
Just wanted to see
the look on your face!

109
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:37,791
Don't be embarrassed.

110
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,708
Rika may not be able to
get you into that game

111
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:41,166
but there's one she can.

112
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,583
Rika has a different
game you could play

113
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:45,208
where you might have
a similar experience.

114
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,541
Are you serious?

115
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,708
How in the world do you
have something like that?

116
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:50,500
After Rika helped
them develop it.

117
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:52,750
They let her keep a
copy of the prototype.

118
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,166
Wanna try it out?

119
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,666
Yeah. Of course!

120
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,125
So what? You put this on?

121
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:00,958
Yep. It's the newest
head mount display

122
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:03,375
from a game development
company called Largehard

123
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:05,375
and it hasn't even
been released.

124
00:06:05,458 --> 00:06:07,625
But when it finally is these
things are gonna be huge.

125
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:09,208
Also included is
the demo version

126
00:06:09,291 --> 00:06:11,208
of this exclusive software.

127
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:13,041
It's basically the
greatest 3D interactive

128
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:15,208
fantasy video game
ever created

129
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:17,583
and it's called,
"Romancing Saga 14!"

130
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:19,291
Why, Saga?

131
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:21,208
Because that's the
prefecture they live in.

132
00:06:21,291 --> 00:06:23,125
That's the reason?

133
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,083
It's pitch black!
I can't see a thing!

134
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:30,750
Be patient, the
software's still loading.

135
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,958
It won't be
much longer now.

136
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:48,791
Saga. It is the
final frontier.

137
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,333
Ah, that's not cool.

138
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,125
To bring an
end to this world

139
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:54,625
the reigning governor
of Saga took action.

140
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:56,458
He summoned the
Prince of Darkness

141
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,000
from another dimension.

142
00:06:58,083 --> 00:07:00,666
In order to
destroy the Earth.

143
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:04,041
The opening is long,
so Rika will skip it!

144
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:05,375
Hey! Don't do that,

145
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:07,541
I was really interested
in the Valhalla Castle!

146
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:08,875
Sorry, too late!

147
00:07:08,958 --> 00:07:10,375
First you have
to pick a profession

148
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:11,875
and that'll determine
the specific attributes

149
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:13,500
of your characters.

150
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,416
Valhalla Castle.

151
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:20,541
Right. So.

152
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:22,583
Maybe I'll be this.

153
00:07:26,291 --> 00:07:27,541
Hey, over here!

154
00:07:30,041 --> 00:07:32,416
Oh wow. That's some
outfit you got there!

155
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,666
Rika chose 'gunner' and
this is what it gave her.

156
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,916
You don't look half
bad yourself, Kodaka.

157
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,416
Wish I could see.

158
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,750
You can! Just select 'equipment'
from the main menu

159
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,458
and it'll show you
what you look like.

160
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:46,250
What the hell is this?

161
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:48,916
I chose 'wizard', wizards
don't dress like this!

162
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,041
Rika read about this
urban legend that says

163
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:52,833
if you stay a virgin
until you're thirty,

164
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:54,500
you automatically
become a wizard.

165
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:56,791
Rika thinks you look
just about right.

166
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:59,625
Clearly your character made
it to thirty without doing it.

167
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:01,041
I don't wanna be
that kind of wizard!

168
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:02,666
Come on, this is ridiculous;

169
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,458
my guy doesn't even
know any magic!

170
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,916
Rika would guess it is
perhaps an honorary title.

171
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,958
Is this some sick
practical joke?

172
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:10,875
Hey! What's up
with your outfit?

173
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:19,875
I wouldn't talk if
I were you. At all.

174
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,625
Wait just a second!

175
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,458
What the hell stupid
outfit is this,

176
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:26,041
I chose 'blacksmith!'

177
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:28,416
Now that you mention it,
it does sorta look like that.

178
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,791
Please, it does not!

179
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:31,083
I don't remember
'blacksmiths' dressing

180
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:32,833
all slutty like this.

181
00:08:32,916 --> 00:08:35,250
They can call forth
swords using magic.

182
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:38,000
And cut their
enemy to pieces!

183
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:40,458
Actually, that sounds
more like a ninja to Rika.

184
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:41,958
Aww man, I screwed up.

185
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:43,625
I picked the worst
possible job

186
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,750
with the worst
possible outfit.

187
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:48,416
Would you quit your
bitching, Meat?

188
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,583
What are you?

189
00:08:57,208 --> 00:08:59,208
I picked 'rose girl' and
look what it did to me.

190
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:01,000
Looks like the developer
got a little lazy

191
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,750
when he built that one.

192
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,708
But still, check
out your attack prowess

193
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:05,791
and your magic ability!

194
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,750
They're through the roof!

195
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,916
As long as I'm still
strong, I'm okay.

196
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:15,583
You really are in love with
that costume, aren't you?

197
00:09:15,666 --> 00:09:16,958
Not really.

198
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,750
Hey you guys. What do
you think about my outfit?

199
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,458
Well, you uh.
You look very strong.

200
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,500
You're a very authentic
looking Samurai.

201
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,083
Hold on a sec.

202
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:28,791
Sena, Yozora and Yukimura
are obviously the muscle.

203
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:31,791
And Rika's the long
distance attacker. What am I?

204
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:34,791
If Rika had to make an educated
guess, you're worthless.

205
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:37,541
That's not the answer
I was hoping for.

206
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:40,208
I guess the only thing we're
missing now is a healer.

207
00:09:40,291 --> 00:09:42,500
Don't worry guys, I'm here!

208
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:44,250
Maria?

209
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:47,041
You look exactly the same
as you do in real life.

210
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:49,083
So I'm guessing you're
the healer then?

211
00:09:49,166 --> 00:09:50,958
Yep. I've seen
that look before.

212
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:53,750
An acolyte of God is
always an Acolyte of God,

213
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,166
no matter what!

214
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:58,041
Since everybody is
accounted for now,

215
00:09:58,125 --> 00:09:59,958
should we get a move on?

216
00:10:02,916 --> 00:10:04,833
Guys! Check it out!

217
00:10:04,916 --> 00:10:06,083
That's Valhalla Castle.

218
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:08,125
the Prince of
Darkness lives here.

219
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:09,750
This mode is a
simulation that ends

220
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,458
after you defeat
the bad guy.

221
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:14,291
This prince guy can be
beaten in a simulation?

222
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:15,541
Remember what
you're wearing,

223
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,291
this game kinda blows.

224
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,708
Looks like we've
got company.

225
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:25,041
What are they, aliens?

226
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:26,458
They're completely
disgusting.

227
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:27,791
They look and
smell like poo!

228
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:31,833
I know them.

229
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,500
They're Dragon Gobies!

230
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:35,833
Hold on, what the
heck's a Dragon Gobie?

231
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:38,750
Fish that inhabit the
Ariake Sea in Kyushu.

232
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:41,416
I used to eat them
when I lived there!

233
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:43,458
They don't seem
very appetizing.

234
00:10:43,541 --> 00:10:46,083
Of course, to
each his own.

235
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:47,500
They're Dragon
Gobie Soldiers,

236
00:10:47,583 --> 00:10:49,250
the first of the small fry.

237
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:50,583
The only reason
they're in the game

238
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:52,083
is cause they
look like aliens!

239
00:10:52,166 --> 00:10:53,666
Man that's terrible.

240
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:55,166
I don't care what they
are or why they're here,

241
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,250
let's kill 'em!

242
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:57,791
No, stop it!

243
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,916
Don't you feel sorry for them,
being treated like monsters

244
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,291
because of
how they look?

245
00:11:01,375 --> 00:11:03,083
Dragon Gobie's may
be weird looking,

246
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:05,291
but they didn't ask
to be born that way!

247
00:11:05,375 --> 00:11:07,666
Please. Don't hurt them;
just let them go!

248
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:11,125
You're a very good man.

249
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:12,750
With a big heart of gold.

250
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:13,875
When you look
at those fish

251
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,541
you see yourself don't you?

252
00:11:15,625 --> 00:11:17,000
People as good as you.

253
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:18,541
They're hard to find.

254
00:11:18,625 --> 00:11:20,791
Yeah. you're really
the best Kodaka.

255
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:24,000
Thanks guys.

256
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:27,666
Eat this!

257
00:11:29,708 --> 00:11:31,083
Poor little fish!

258
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:32,416
Why are you killing them?

